    IComponent, IEndOfDayPerformer, IExceptionListener, IFIXListener, IFIXMessageProcessor, IHasAttributes, IConfigurable, IRegisterable, IMessageListener, IMessageProcessor, IMessageSource, ICatalysEventListener, Cloneable, EventListener

    public class EMXMessageVerifier
extends FIXListenerBase
    The EMXMessageVerifier is a MessageListener that can be configured to verify none, some or all incoming EMXMessages.

    Any EMXMessage that fails the verification process will be rejected, with an automatically generated MERR being sent back to EMX for forwarding to the originator of the message. In such cases, the message will not be delivered to the client application. In other words, verification failure is not notified to the client application.

    Author:
    John Cameron, Christopher J Burton, 02/Jun/2002.

      • onMessageFromFix

        public void onMessageFromFix(MessageEvent event,
                             IFIXMessage message)
                      throws Exception
        This method is called every time a message is received. If the message is not an EMXMessage, no action is taken. If the message is an EMXMessage, it may be verified (depending on the configuration parameter). If the verification fails, an exception is thrown. This prevents the message from being passed on to the client application.
        Specified by:
        onMessageFromFix in interface IFIXListener
        Overrides:
        onMessageFromFix in class FIXListenerBase
        Parameters:

        message - the message
        Throws:
        Exception - if an exception occurs when processing the message

      • setVerify

        public final void setVerify(int verify)
        Define whether received EMX messages should be verified against our truststore or not. The default, if this method is not called, is no verification.

        The verification policy may be specified via the Properties that are supplied to the setProperties() method. The options that can be passed to this method are:

        • VERIFY_NONE: No incoming messages will be verified;
        • VERIFY_PARTICIPANTS: Messages signed by other participants will be verified;
        • VERIFY_ALL: All messages, including MACKs and MERRs from the EMX Hub and messages signed by EMX Services, will be verified.
        Parameters:
        verify - the verification policy

      • setVerify

        public final void setVerify(String verify)
        Define whether received EMX messages should be verified against our truststore or not. The default, if this method is not called, is no verification.

        The verification policy may be specified via the Properties that are supplied to the setProperties() method. The options that can be passed to this method and for specification via Properties are:

        • verify=NONE: No incoming messages will be verified;
        • verify=PARTICIPANTS: Messages signed by other participants will be verified;
        • verify=ALL: All messages, including MACKs and MERRs from the EMX Hub and messages signed by EMX Services, will be verified.
        Parameters:
        verify - the verification policy
